es of MY class!&quot; in the balancing discussions/flame wars.  Give me a break. <br>
<br>
In one example when I actually tried to say something, it was in tells to a guildmate I'd grouped with a number of times -- I'd be much less likely to say anything to someone I didn't know -- and I tried to be as nice as possible and just make a suggestion to try.  It didn't go over well. I took a similar approach with another cleric in my guild once and he was actually very receptive.  He grouped with us a lot and later told me how surprised he was to learn a lot about how to play his cleric from a warrior of all things (was before i'd played a cleric much).  I was very pleasantly surprised.  It's the former people that peeve me... when you're trying to be as nice as you can about something they could obviously work on and ya just get snapped at.  <br>
<br>
Long winded? I'm always long winded.  It's a sickness.<br>
